      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "The reason you need a &quot;default no argument constructor&quot; FooClass() is likely because Spring follows the JavaBean Specification, which requires this to work for automatically marshalling and unmarshalling when serializing and deserializing objects."
