    "question_id" : 7625783,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Generally, this error comes because we <strong>don’t make default constructor</strong>.<br />\nBut in my case:<br />\nThe issue was coming only due to I have made <strong>used object class inside parent class</strong>.<br />\nThis has wasted my whole day.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 11643977,
      "reputation" : 61,
      "user_id" : 9054165,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-3jxW3uE7shQ/AAAAAAAAAAI/AAAAAAAABRo/w5sSz3emctA/s256-rj/photo.jpg",
      "display_name" : "Felipe Ceballos",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/9054165/felipe-ceballos"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 6,
    "last_activity_date" : 1556131631,
    "creation_date" : 1556131631,
    "answer_id" : 55836691,
    "question_id" : 7625783,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Regarding the last publication I had the same problem where using Lombok 1.18.* generated the problem.</p>\n\n<p>My solution was to add @NoArgsConstructor (constructor without parameters), since @Data includes by default @RequiredArgsConstructor (Constructor with parameters).</p>\n\n<p>lombok Documentation\n<a href=\"https://projectlombok.org/features/all\" rel=\"noreferrer\">https://projectlombok.org/features/all</a></p>\n\n<p>That would solve the problem:</p>\n\n<pre><code>package example.counter;\n\nimport javax.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n\nimport lombok.Data;\n\n@Data\n@NoArgsConstructor\npublic class CounterRequest {\n    @NotNull\n    private final Integer int1;\n\n    @NotNull\n    private final Integer int2;\n}\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
